# tina4-php — Cursor Rules

Tina4 PHP v3.10.46. 54 built-in features, zero external dependencies. PHP 8.2+.

## Key Patterns

```php
use Tina4\Router;

Router::get("/api/users", function($request, $response) {
    return $response->json(["users" => []], 200);
});

Router::post("/api/users", function($request, $response) {
    return $response->json(["created" => $request->body["name"]], 201);
})->noAuth();
```

## Critical Rules

- Route methods are static: `Router::get()` not `$router->get()`
- POST/PUT/DELETE require auth by default — chain `->noAuth()` to make public
- GET is public by default — chain `->secure()` to protect
- ORM conversion: `asArray()` not `toArray()`
- Queue job payload: `$job->payload` not `$job->data`
- Namespace: `Tina4\` — e.g., `Tina4\Router`, `Tina4\ORM`, `Tina4\Auth`
- Templates are Twig syntax (not Blade)
- Default port: 7146
- Entry point: `new \Tina4\App(basePath: __DIR__); $app->start();`

## Project Structure

Routes in `src/routes/`, ORM in `src/orm/`, templates in `src/templates/`, static in `src/public/`.

See llms.txt for complete API reference.
